  "prompt": "When a parking sign says 2-hour parking from 8 to 5 on Monday-Friday, what does it mean for the remainder of the time?",
  "response": "When a parking sign specifies \"2-hour parking from 8 to 5 on Monday-Friday,\" it means that during those hours on weekdays, you are allowed to park for a maximum of two hours. Outside of these times\u2014such as evenings after 5 PM, weekends (Saturday and Sunday), and overnight\u2014the parking restriction does not apply. \n\nThis implies that you can park for longer than two hours outside of the specified period, or there may be no time limit at all during those times, depending on other posted regulations or local parking laws. Always check for additional signs or local ordinances to ensure you comply with all parking rules.",
